version_description: The chords for this song are simple enough but the chord changes are a bit fast. To add the higher harmonies in the recording, barre the A and G chords on the 5th and 3rd frets for the intro.
It's the acoustic version of the song. Got the chords by watching this cover https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ojhyZnlIOaY. It's on standard tuning and have capo on the second fret.
Here is a standard tuning which probably same as Taylor does.
Mainly made this to be played on piano.
No capo, maj7 and m7 chords used in bridge.

This specific tab is based off an acoustic cover made by Chanele Mc Guinness (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gv_EsZn4fzk). Due to it being a cover, the lyrics are slightly different the the original. Watch the video to see the picking pattern. Standard tuning, capo on third fret.
